Data Fields

EDMA_queueEntryInfo_t outstandingEntries [EDMA_NUM_QUEUE_ENTRIES]
 Outstanding entries are entries in the queue at the moment of status query that have not yet been serviced. The number of relevant entries in this array is numOutstandingEntries.
 
EDMA_queueEntryInfo_t dequeuedEntries [EDMA_NUM_QUEUE_ENTRIES]
 Dequeued entries are entries in the queue at the moment of querying the queue status that have been serviced, the number of relevant entries in this array is EDMA_NUM_QUEUE_ENTRIES. More...
 
bool isThresholdExceeded
 status whether queue threshold is exceeded.
 
uint8_t maxQueueEntries
 Maximum number of entries ever in the queue since EDMA became operational (after reset), if this maximum ever exceeded the set queue threshold and queue thresholding were enabled, it would trigger error condition.
 
uint8_t numOutstandingEntries
 Number of outstanding (not yet serviced) entries in the queue, QSTATN::NUMVAL in EDMA UG.

EDMA_queueEntryInfo_t EDMA_queueStatusInfo_t_::dequeuedEntries[EDMA_NUM_QUEUE_ENTRIES]

Dequeued entries are entries in the queue at the moment of querying the queue status that have been serviced, the number of relevant entries in this array is EDMA_NUM_QUEUE_ENTRIES.
